This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image sentiment analysis using Convolutional Neural Networks. It also involves Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques, which suggests it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The use of deep networks for training and transfer learning suggests it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which suggests it could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of images and videos in social media suggests it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
